{{Quote|Having been a life-long ''Star Wars'' fan, I wanted to help capture that spirit of fun, cleverness and visual interest. Hopefully all the imagery will get people in the mood and the spirit of that world.|Van Ling|<ref name="TPM DVD">{{SWArchive|url=episode-i/release/video/f20010927/index.html|text=Van Ling: On the DVD Menu}}</ref>}}
'''Van Ling''' is the artist who created the menus for the [[Star Wars home video releases|DVDs]] of [[George Lucas]]' six [[Star Wars saga|''Star Wars'' saga]] films and the DVDs for the ''[[Star Wars: Clone Wars]]'' animated series. He also gathered behind-the-scenes imagery to produce the DVD included with the Limited Edition of ''[[Sculpting a Galaxy: Inside the Star Wars Model Shop]]''. Ling additionally created screen graphics and other material for the preshow queue of "[[Star Tours: The Adventures Continue]]" for the Disneyland theme parks around the world.

